<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,582,969]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[269,493,798,825]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" refId="ref369190" refString="Rondani, C. (1863) Diptera exotica revisa et annotata novis nonnullis descriptis. Eredi Soliani, Modena, 99 pp., 1 pl. [This is the separate that came out before the journal version with a different title, here as Rondani (1864 a)]." type="book" year="1863">Rondani (1863: 62)</bibRefCitation>
described both sexes of 
<taxonomicName box="[781,1016,798,824]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corrigiolata">
<emphasis box="[781,1016,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Anthrax corrigiolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from specimens received from R.A. Philippi, to whom he attributed the species name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, A." box="[754,941,834,860]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="13 - 48" refId="ref348459" refString="Costa, A. (1866) Acquisti fatti durante l'anno 1863. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della Regia Universita di Napoli, 3, 13 - 48." type="journal article" year="1866">
<collectingRegion box="[754,818,834,860]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Costa</collectingRegion>
(1866: 37)
</bibRefCitation>
listed a single MZUN specimen (as 
<taxonomicName authority="Phil." authorityName="Phil." class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corrigiolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Anthrax corrigiolata</emphasis>
Phil.
</taxonomicName>
) numbered “832”. We found just 
<specimenCount box="[770,893,870,897]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[900,987,871,897]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">syntype</typeStatus>
in this study. The male 
<typeStatus box="[1252,1344,870,896]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">syntype</typeStatus>
(s) is/are presumed lost. 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J." box="[369,763,906,932]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" refId="ref349891" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J. (1999) World catalog of bee flies (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, 756 pp." type="book" year="1999">Evenhuis &amp; Greathead (1999: 432)</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly assumed the single remaining female 
<typeStatus box="[1320,1407,907,933]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">syntype</typeStatus>
in the MZUN to be a 
<typeStatus box="[411,513,942,968]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
